reviews.headline: This DRAMA is tacky‚Ä¶
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] Honestly, for all the hype around this product I expected more. I wanted to love this mascara, I have always enjoyed Lanc√¥me products and how luxurious it feels to use them, but I think this mascara missed the mark. Let me start by saying this mascara looks incredible. One coat is indeed a very dramatic difference. The issue is it claims to be waterproof, and I suppose in a roundabout way it is, but the mascara never fully dries. The entire time I wore it (an 8 hour work day and then a social event after) it was tacky. Sticky like when your lash glue is ready to stick your lashes to. Multiple times through the day I had to use a lash comb to unstick my corner lashes from one another. That seems crazy to me, and I did wonder if it was user error and maybe the layers needed to dry in between coats like nail polish, but no, dear reader, that is not the case.

reviews.headline: New go-to!
reviews.comments:
[I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I've been using the Lanc√¥me Hypn√¥se Drama Waterproof Mascara for a couple weeks now, and it's become a reliable go-to in my makeup bag. What I love most is its buildability ‚Äî you can easily layer it for a more dramatic look without it clumping or getting heavy. Whether I want a softer, everyday lash or a full-on voluminous effect, it handles both beautifully.

As for waterproofing, it truly lives up to the claim. It doesn't smudge or flake, even through long days, sweaty workouts, or the occasional tearful moment. Yet, it's not impossibly stubborn to remove at night with a good eye makeup remover.

I also appreciate how well it holds a curl. My lashes stay lifted all day, which really opens up the eyes. It gives impressive volume, making lashes look fuller and thicker with just one or two coats, while still keeping a nice separation ‚Äî no spider lashes here.

Overall, if you're looking for a mascara that delivers on volume, keeps lashes defined, holds a curl, and truly withstands water, this one's a standout. Highly recommend!

faceoff_positive.comments:
[I received this product in exchange for my honest review] 
If you're on the hunt for a mascara that truly delivers drama and doesn't quit halfway through the day, Lanc√¥me Hypn√¥se Drama Waterproof Mascaramight just be your new go-to. With its signature S-shaped brush and intensely black formula, this mascara gives lashes serious volume from the very first coat. It lifts, thickens, and fans out lashes for a bold, eye-opening look that holds up through just about anything‚Äîrain, humidity, even tears.

One of the standout features is just how long-lasting and waterproof it is. Once it's on, it stays put all day without smudging or flaking. It's especially great if you live in a humid climate, have oily lids, or just need a mascara that can survive long days (and nights). Even better, it holds a curl exceptionally well, making it ideal for those with naturally straight lashes.

That said, the waterproof power comes with a trade-off: removal can be a bit trickyYou'll definitely want a good oil-based makeup remover on hand to avoid tugging or lash fallout. And because the formula is quite thick, it's easy to go overboard if you're not careful‚Äîwiping off excess product from the brush or using a lash comb can help avoid clumps.

Also worth noting: if you have very sensitive eyes or wear contacts this formula might be a little too intense. Some users report slight irritation during removal, so it may not be the best choice for daily wear if your eyes are easily bothered.

Overall, Lanc√¥me Hypn√¥se Drama Waterproof Mascara delivers exactly what it promises: dramatic, voluminous lashes with serious staying power. It's not the most low-maintenance option out there, but for those special occasions‚Äîor just days when you want your lashes to look their absolute best‚Äîit definitely rises to the occasion.
faceoff_positive.headline: Love

faceoff_negative.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I have long, curly, thick lashes that honestly work great with most mascaras. I have been looking for a nice high end waterproof mascara but honestly this is not it. I will say that while it stays on all day, I have noticed it smudging and flaking especially when wet (I have watery eyes). I hate do not like the shape of the wand, I have to keep rotating it as I apply it so it takes sooo long for me to get my lashes to look good. The formula is super wet but the wand doesn't comb through the lashes, just clumps up and creates clumpy spider lashes. It also pushes my lashes back so I ALWAYS get mascara on my eyelids (then I have to touch up my eyeshadow). For me to make it look good I need to use a lash separator or a different mascara, so for that reason, I wouldn't recommend it. Maybe it's meant for different lash types but it takes too much effort for me to make it look good.
